                                                MRS Oil Nigeria PLC
                                             Company Snapshot
                                            









                                            
	MRS Oil Nigeria PLC operates in the Petroleum products sector.
	
	In addition to historical fundamental analyses, the complete report available to purchase compares MRS Oil Nigeria PLC with three other
	
			companies in this sector in Nigeria:
		
	Forte Oil PLC
	
		(2016
	sales of 148.61 billion Naira [US$425.01  million]
		of which 82%
		was Fuels),
	
	Conoil Public Limited Company
	
		(85.02 billion Naira [US$243.17  million]
		of which 94%
		was White Products), and
	
	Mobil Oil Nigeria PLC
	
		(94.11 billion Naira [US$269.15  million]
		of which 100%
		was Petroleum Products Marketing).
	
	Sales Analysis. 
	MRS Oil Nigeria PLC reported sales of 109.64 billion Naira (US$313.56 million)
		for the
		
		year ending
		December of 2016.
	
		This
		
			represents
		
				an
			
			increase of 25.9%
		
		 versus 2015, when the company's sales were 87.10 billion Naira.
	
		Sales of Lubes saw an increase
		
			of
		37.2% in 2016, from
		2.49 billion Naira to 3.42 billion Naira.
		
			Not all segments of MRS Oil Nigeria PLC experienced an increase in sales in 2016:
			sales of Aviation fell 13.0% to 9.63 billion Naira.
			

	




 


 
 


 
 


 
 











 



 













 










